<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/590.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The towns to the north and within 10 miles of Port au Prince have fallen,
                            and it appears impossible for the Government to survive many hours
                            longer.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>